snippet.textDisplay: This song scratches at the film that separates the physical realm and the ethereal realm. A compositional masterpiece. The only thing which could have made it another level better, in my humble opinion, would be if the Tabla entered with the Shehnai and instead of single notes, played a steady Rajasthani chaal till the end. That would bring the song full circle thematically by returning to the song's rich folk grounding. But regardless, this song is a masterpiece. Hands down.
snippet.textOriginal: This song scratches at the film that separates the physical realm and the ethereal realm. A compositional masterpiece. The only thing which could have made it another level better, in my humble opinion, would be if the Tabla entered with the Shehnai and instead of single notes, played a steady Rajasthani chaal till the end. That would bring the song full circle thematically by returning to the song's rich folk grounding. But regardless, this song is a masterpiece. Hands down.
